This would also lead to really weird UX problems. Say I download a replication archive from a paper that records Julia 1.10.0 in the manifest. That replication code works around a bug in 1.10.0. The bug has since been fixed in 1.10.1, but the replication code actually depends on the presence of the bug, so it won't run correctly under 1.10.1. As a user of that code, what am I supposed to do now? Uninstall 1.10.1 entirely from my system to force Juliaup to actually run with the version that is recorded in the manifest? I will now also get a different version of Julia when running depending on (completely unrelated) channels I have installed, that also seems really weird.

The worry about binary bloat in terms of installed Julia versions of course is real. But I think we should try to fix that via UX. For example, the launcher could print a notice when it starts a project, and the compat section in the `Project.toml` suggests that a newer version of Julia could be used for that project. It could even offer an interactive option "hey, you are running with a project that is using an outdated Julia version" or something like that.

(As a side note, I just checked, my `.julia` folder is at 27GB. If we want to fight binary bloat, there seems some other villain in town ;)","created_at":"2024-10-06T06:07:46Z","updated_at":"2024-10-06T06:07:46Z","html_url":"https://github.com/JuliaLang/juliaup/pull/1059#discussion_r1788910151","pull_request_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/juliaup/pulls/1059","author_association":"COLLABORATOR","_links":{"self":{"href":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/juliaup/pulls/comments/1788910151"},"html":{"href":"https://github.com/JuliaLang/juliaup/pull/1059#discussion_r1788910151"},"pull_request":{"href":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/juliaup/pulls/1059"}},"reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/juliaup/pulls/comments/1788910151/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"start_line":null,"original_start_line":null,"start_side":null,"line":472,"original_line":472,"side":"RIGHT","in_reply_to_id":1788687898,"original_position":165,"position":180,"subject_type":"line"},"pull_request":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/juliaup/pulls/1059","id":2108582211,"node_id":"PR_kwDOEE6KR859rmlD","html_url":"https://github.com/JuliaLang/juliaup/pull/1059","diff_url":"https://github.com/JuliaLang/juliaup/pull/1059.diff","patch_url":"https://github.com/JuliaLang/juliaup/pull/1059.patch","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/juliaup/issues/1059","number":1059,"state":"open","locked":false,"title":"Launch the manifest-specified Julia version","user":{"login":"tecosaur","id":20903656,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjIwOTAzNjU2","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/20903656?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/tecosaur","html_url":"https://github.com/tecosaur","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tecosaur/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tecosaur/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.c